    "created_at": "2014-08-27T17:01:26Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-08-27T17:01:26Z",
    "body": "The primary problem that I have is that is that, in that const\\* does **NOT** imply that the memory that is pointing at is mutable. In fact, C libraries do not tend to maintain const correctness at all, especially since failing to be const correct tends to cascade down to consuming libraries.\n\nIn rust, *mut implies that the memory being pointed to can be mutated, which again, is just not correct. I would be much happier if *mut c_char was simply *c_char which implies nothing.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "reactions": {
