    "created_at": "2014-08-27T17:11:39Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-08-27T17:11:39Z",
    "body": "@carllerche if you mean that the wording is misleading, that may be true -- certainly `*mut T` is intended to mean \"the type system allows you to mutate this\" not \"it is definitely safe to mutate this!\". I think a lot of the usability and casting problems you are seeing is because a `*mut T` should really be silently coercable to `*const T` (as in C). The fact that it is not seems like a bug. I plan on opening an RFC about this, don't anticipate any reason for it not to sail through.\n\nIn this particular case, for example, returning a `*mut T` should be strictly more convenient, from a casting point of view, as a `*const T`.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
